Please answer my code questions using the given API following this format: <<<api>>>: $API
<<<code>>>: $CODE
<<<explanation>>>: $EXPLANATION.
For API Iterator.next, the API usage rule is: Get the next element from an Iterator if it has more elements.

Question: I want to split a value which is stored in a String while using window handles: :This is my codeSet<String> winHandle = driver.getWindowHandles();System.out.println(winHandle);I want to split winHandle. The value I get when i print the winHandle is like this [{0dd5d2e3-da7f-4a57-ad06-52c19336d3c6}, {a32fd7a5-040f-488f-8bc0-64d9a4496509}]I want to select the Second Value {a32fd7a5-040f-488f-8bc0-64d9a4496509}
Please using this api: Iterator.next.
Answer:
response:
<<<api>>>: Iterator.next()

<<<code>>>: 
Iterator<String> iterator = winHandle.iterator();
iterator.next();
String secondValue = iterator.next();

<<<explanation>>>: 
To split the value stored in the String and select the second value, you can use the Iterator.next() method. First, create an iterator object by calling the iterator() method on the winHandle Set. Then, call the next() method twice on the iterator object to skip the first value and retrieve the second value. Assign the second value to a String variable (in this case, "secondValue") for further use.
